    {
      "id": "6c9cd26f_02f1518b",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "message": "good to see a early preview and now I can give you some suggestions\n\n\nmy main issue is the use of dmiPluginTrustLevelCache I think it is more complicated then it needs to be I dont need you  need properties but just a map of dmi(Data?!)Server names to status(enum)\n\nalso out code should be consistent in using the name 'dmi' or 'dmiPLugin' it is very inconsistent now.\nRelated to this you need to understand that the dmi plugin is split in a model and a date service which are you monitoering here?! I am note sure I think this is a Stakehodler question ie open issue!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2023-08-30 07:37:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "ac95f3e5_474c0a0a",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "message": "As discussed regarding the approach.\n- we dont really need the Application Events here and we can way better using the scheduler which calls the dmi plugin after pre-configured time and check the status of the dmi-plugin\n- in my opinion we wont be having that much number of dmi-plugins in the network. ( dmi-plugins would be managing thousands of devices ) but here we dont care about the number of devices. we just want healthcheck of dmi-plugins only.\n- Look at the ModuleSyncWatchdog to get an idea and an example approach for you.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7965,
        "name": "Priyank Maheshwari",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "priyank.maheshwari@est.tech",
        "username": "mpriyank"
      },
      "updated": "2023-08-30 11:23:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "95d65a8e_da55cc38",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "message": "You are right. If there were not thousands of DMI plugins, there would be no need to have a multi-threaded (currently 3), parallel, DMI plugin availability check approach. \n\nI can revert the current solution to a Spring's @Scheduled(fixedDelayString=30000) annotation-based solution.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2023-08-30 11:38:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ac95f3e5_474c0a0a",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "3c618523_4bbb576d",
